The topics handled within the subjects comprise mainly company's both short-term (connected with working capital management) and long-term or strategic (i.e. connected with financing, investing and dividend growth) decisions.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The course gives basic knowledge 
about the main concepts of corporate financeLearning outcomes/õpiväljund:  A student, who has passed the subject, has obtained the knowledge about the basis of financial management, including theoretical terms and concepts; for solving practical-theoretical cases in financial management; the role of financial manager in a company and the importance about the financial management and it's connection with financial market and other areas in the economy (especially with the financial accounting). A student, who has passed the subject, has obtained the ability to implement the concepts and methods used in financial management in practical situations, including the ability to orientate in theory of time value of money; owns the overview about the different financial sources for the company; knows different theories of dividend and capital structure; can calculate the company's cost of capital and form it's optimal capital structure; knows, how to evaluate the profitability of different projects through previously performed financial analysis and planning; is able to implement the methods used in working capital management; has obtained the basic knowledge of value creation and valuation of a company, about mergers and acquisitions and also bankruptcy and restructuring.
